io.mosip.registration.service.login

Interface LoginService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LoginServiceImpl

    public interface LoginService
    The LoginService represents to fetch the information related to authentication data, user data, center data, screen authorization data and validating the user and updating table on every login attempt. This will also handle initial sync which will happen before loading login screen.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Sravya Surampalli

      • initialSync

        List<String> initialSync()
        Execute global param, master sync, user detail, user salt detail and key policy sync's as a initial sync

        If Initial setup is enabled and TPM is enabled:

        Exceute TPM PublicKeySyncService:

        Keyindex will be returned being used in other sync in case of initial setup

        Execute PublicKey Sync, Global Param Sync, Master Sync, User Detail Sync, User Salt Detail Sync:

        If all above sync are success:

        return Success as status

        If any sync is failed

        return Failure as status

        Returns:
        List list of sync results

      • validateInvalidLogin

        String validateInvalidLogin(UserDTO userDTO,
                            String errorMessage,
                            int invalidLoginCount,
                            int invalidLoginTime)
        This method will Validate login attempts to check whether operator can login or not

        This will validate against invalid number of attempts and time and update the table with the corresponding parameters in case of invalid or valid

        Parameters:
        userDTO - UserDTO user details
        errorMessage - String error message for validation
        invalidLoginCount - Integer invalid login count against which validation will be done
        invalidLoginTime - Integer invalid login time against which validation will be done
        Returns:
        String returns whether validation successful or not

      • validateUser

        ResponseDTO validateUser(String userId)
        This method will Validate user id entered by operator

        If User exists :

        Fetch the center id mapped to user id entered by operator

        Fetch the roles mapped to user id

        The success response DTO will be formed and returned from this method.

        If Roles not matches or exists:

        The failure response DTO will be formed and returned from this method.

        If Center id not matches or exists

        The failure response DTO will be formed and returned from this method.

        If user not exists :

        The failure response DTO will be formed and returned from this method.

        Parameters:
        userId - String user-id entered by operator
        Returns:
        ResponseDTO based on the result the response DTO will be formed and return to the caller.
